                            <comment id="426601" author="qian_wc" created="Mon, 2 Sep 2024 01:48:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem happens very rare.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Search the Maloo failure on sanity-pcc/test_40, it just happened 1 time in the passed month.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And Patrick&apos;s patch once fixed it simply on b_es6_0:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/ex/lustre-release/+/47158/22/lustre/tests/sanity-pcc.sh&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/ex/lustre-release/+/47158/22/lustre/tests/sanity-pcc.sh&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        # Occasionally async can take a tiny bit longer due to races, that&apos;s OK
	[ $time1 -le $((time2 + 1)) ] ||
		echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Total time &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; async open attach should be smaller&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will do the same fix on the master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
